    <stitle>POWER STEERING PUMP: EATON MODEL BB135 R, L - FILTER ELEMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
        <title>FILTER ELEMENT</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>After a major power steering system failure requiring replacement or major overhaul, the system
                    must be purged and a new filter installed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a suction gun, remove fluid from the reservoir through the filler opening or remove
                return hose to drain reservoir.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard retaining clip from reservoir cover and body.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cover from reservoir by holding down spring loaded cover and removing wing nut,
                washer and gasket (
                <hotlnk document="s05006w_1.xml" xrefid="f0500602">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Take out spring, filter cap and filter.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install replacement filter, filter cap and spring (
                <hotlnk document="s05006w_1.xml" xrefid="f0500602">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Install gasket, cover, washer and
                wing nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill reservoir to the cold mark with specified transmission fluid. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s05006w_16.xml" xrefid="hl0500601">LUBRICATE</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
